_json.description: Richard Albert Mohler, Jr. (born October 19, 1959), is an American historical theologian and the ninth president of the Southern Baptist Theological Seminary in Louisville, Kentucky. He has been described as "one of America's most influential evangelicals". He blogs on his website and hosts "The Briefing," a daily podcast on current events from the Christian perspective. As a Calvinist, Mohler believes that human salvation is a free gift from God which cannot be earned by human action or will.
